  More than thirty thousand Nigerians are now down with the Coronavirus, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. According to a tweet released by the NCDC on Wednesday night, the country recorded 460 new cases, bringing the total number of confirmed cases so far to 30, 249, with 12, 373 persons discharged. The breakdown of figures recorded according to states is as follows: Lagos-150 Rivers-49 Oyo-43 Delta-38 FCT-26 Anambra-20 Kano-20 Plateau-18 Edo-14 Bayelsa-13 Enugu-13 Osun-12 Kwara-10 Borno-8 Ogun-7 Kaduna-6 Imo-4 Bauchi-3 Gombe-3 Niger-2 Adamawa-1 684 persons have so far lost their lives in Nigeria due to Coronavirus, the tweet said.  460 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-150Rivers-49Oyo-43Delta-38FCT-26Anambra-20Kano-20Plateau-18Edo-14Bayelsa-13Enugu-13Osun-12Kwara-10Borno-8Ogun-7Kaduna-6Imo-4Bauchi-3Gombe-3Niger-2 Adamawa-1 30,249 confirmed12,373 discharged684 deaths pic.twitter.com/uSvoIwWR3R â€” NCDC (@NCDCgov) July 8, 2020 